lead_paragraph: "We want things clear," the photographer Velibor Bozovic said. "When we look at something, we want it to have an instant meaning, and we need to understand what we're looking at. These photographs don't provide that."
snippet: Velibor Bozovic's photographs of Eastern Europe almost look familiar, as Shane Dixon Kavanaugh reports. But everything is slightly off.
